This is because all entries in this table are disabled while being recomputed and disabling the entry for itself modifies the contents of the table being recomputed. Thus, recomputing the CS Tables Definition Table checksum is not recommended.

Cause:

This event indicates an error at startup as CS is initializing access to the Critical Data Store. Subsequent CDS errors are ignored by CS.
